name: DeepLearning.AI
Summary: We just released "Large Language Models with Semantic Search”, built with Cohere, and taught by Jay Alammar and Luis Serrano. Search is a key part of many applications. Say, you need to retrieve documents or products in response to a user query; how can LLMs help? You’ll learn about (i) Embeddings, to retrieve a collection of documents loosely related to a query, and (ii) LLM assisted re-ranking, to rank them precisely according to relevance. You’ll also go through code showing how to tie all this together to build a complete search system for retrieving relevant Wikipedia articles. Please check it out! https://www.deeplearning.ai/.../large-language-models.../

name: DeepLearning.AI
Summary: Meet Adrian, who’s #LearningFrom Tampa Bay, Florida!“As an engineer, I am always looking for ways to build my skills to optimize and secure WiFi and Network infrastructure performance. After doing a bit of research, I decided to take the Supervised Machine Learning: Regression and Classification offered by DeepLearning.AI and Stanford University. I learned to analyze data from past WiFi usage and how to make predictions about the best channel or frequency. I also learned how to analyze network traffic patterns and identify unusual activity that may indicate a security breach or identify potential bottlenecks. I’m at the beginning of my learning journey and eager to continue. My advice to other learners would be to start with the fundamentals and practice. The best way to learn is to apply what you learn in the courses. Collaborate with others to stay motivated and strengthen your weak areas. Stay up to date because the machine learning field is constantly evolving. Machine learning can be challenging, but be patient and don’t give up.”
